Company Description

We are in Business for People, empowering people in service organizations with innovative Enterprise and Business software solutions. We’ve innovated and taken a new approach to delivering ERP that works for people. Self-driving, adaptive and intuitive software that is changing the way people work. Our solutions empower people and deliver a better people experience so people can spend time on meaningful high value work they live for.
 Read more on our website about how we transform work and how people feel about it, so our customers and their people can thrive.

Job Description

As a Business Analyst:

 You will execute cross-product and cross-functional product strategy and develop business cases for new or existing products and localizations;
 You will contribute to the functional product roadmap within your domain and help identify and recommend buy, partner and build alternatives;
 You act as a customer during the development phase to make sure that product solutions meet customer’s needs and wants and meets the business/market requirements.
 You translate market requirements and business cases into solid design specifications and assists both Software Engineers and Test Analysts with understanding those requirements;
 You will create user stories and detailed business requirements documentation, in which you can and will prioritize


Qualifications


You have a Bachelor or Master degree in Business Administration or experience on software sector;
 Your knowledge and engaging manner makes it easy for you to get business benefits across to consultants and customers;
 You have a commercial mindset;
 You have a strong analytical mind and a good understanding and knowhow of product marketing, product management and/or software development and services related to business software;
 Your English is fluent.


Additional Information

A chance to participate in the development of an international leading software firm. At Unit4, you have the freedom and autonomy to be successful. An attractive salary while working in a challenging international environment. Enthusiastic colleagues who like to learn from each other. At Unit4 we invest in your personal and professional growth. We don't focus on how many days you work, we trust you on delivering results - thus, we have an unlimited vacation policy.

Job Responsibility



Work closely with the finance and IT department in headquarter of the group, as well as with third party service providers and auditors, to build and improve operational finance related processes and IT system;


Collect information and documents from business teams to ensure successful month end closing and reporting based on the instructions from accounting and group reporting team;


Support business departments with finance related questions;


Support country finance controller to carry out the monthly analysis and budgeting review, and ensure submitted forecasts are in‐line with the business environment and in compliant with Group reporting requirements;


Perform cost control of daily expenditures. Review purchase invoices for accuracy and approved for payment within established agreements;


Ensure established internal control procedures are well followed and performed;


Develop local finance and internal control procedures in compliant with Group reporting policies;


Performing the controller role in the absence of the financial controller;


Provide support for or lead various finance related projects as needed;


Other Ad hoc assignments and business case analysis.



 As the Role Develops
 As the company is growing very rapidly, both in terms of product diversity and geographical footprint, the role is expected to develop accordingly. The candidate is therefore expected to be able to expand into other areas like bigger scope of controlling responsibilities, and new market entries in Germany and other European countries.


 Requirements


 Professional Qualification：

Bachelor or master’s degree in accounting, finance, business or similar;


Good knowledge of local German accounting and tax regulations, IFRS, US GAAP, SOX knowledge is a plus;


5-8 years’ experience from international corporation, auditing or consulting experience is a plus;


Strong communication skills in English and German, Chinese language skill is a plus;


Knowledge of SAP and automative industry experience is an advantage;


Advanced Microsoft office skills, additional data analysis skill is a plus;


Full working rights in Germany, and currently being based in Germany.



 Personal Characteristics:

Proactive and willing to take ownership of assignments;


Always deliver work within deadline and with good quality;


A good team player with international mindset;


Embrace entrepreneur spirit, and willing to grow together with the quick expansion of the company business.



 This position locates in office in Munich, Germany and reports to the country finance controller. Occasional business travelling is needed.
